data.description: Welcome to Sandy Run, and 1261 University Drive, a custom, Mickey Schrenk build. This picturesque neighborhood has older trees and lovely streets with fantastic curb appeal. When I say this home has storage....there is an abundance of space and storage at 4,000 square feet. Do you work from home? The original owners of this corner lot, split level, added a large home office with exterior entry and it is absolutely large enough for multiple workspaces.  The office space can be utilized for a multitude of reasons, including a potential mud room, additional storage space, pet space, study area, or play room, etc.  Hosting guests? There is also an abundance of parking. Walk up the custom paver walkway from either the new driveway (2020) or from Pratt Drive to the front entry and into the foyer. On this entry level is a spacious and comfortable gathering space with wood beamed ceilings, a wood burning fireplace, and custom built ins with easy access to the back patio. Relax outdoors under the covered patio and enjoy the trees and the privacy. Also located on this level is the convenient laundry room with an additional access door to the back patio. In the room just off of the home office, there is even more storage space which can be utilized for sports storage, bulk items, office supplies, etc. The next level up is the kitchen with huge windows facing the backyard, an eat in-kitchen and stainless appliances (2021). This floor is finished off with a formal dining room and large, formal living room with sunlight streaming in through the large windows. The upstairs level has four bedrooms and two full baths. Three of the bedrooms face the front yard and the primary bedroom off the back of the house boasts new flooring and a beautiful a custom closet with plentiful storage and ensuite bathroom. The top floor is the bonus floor which was added when the home was built and provides another private living space with a full kitchen, living room, two bedrooms and full bathroom....the uses for this are endless. This level does have access to an attic space for more storage and hosts the new air conditioning air handlers (2022). But wait, there is a basement level which can be utilized in a variety of ways and offers even more storage....see?  Lots of storage in this house!
